<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="27" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,634,1780]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,350,783,809]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[358,467,784,810]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">Holotype</typeStatus>
dimensions: Hw 36.0; abdomen 40.0; total length 51.0. Head of male 
<typeStatus box="[1301,1403,784,810]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">holotype</typeStatus>
as in 
<typeStatus box="[180,282,821,847]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gonzalez-Soriano" authorityYear="2010" box="[321,449,821,846]" class="Insecta" family="Amphipterygidae" genus="Amphipteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nataliae">
<emphasis box="[321,449,821,846]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">A. nataliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but with narrow black border around labrum and with ventral margin of anteclypeus infused with yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,634,1780]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">
Prothorax as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gonzalez-Soriano" authorityYear="2010" box="[381,510,896,921]" class="Insecta" family="Amphipterygidae" genus="Amphipteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nataliae">
<emphasis box="[381,510,896,921]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">A. nataliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but with pale green pleural spots of middle lobe extending dorsally toward, but not touching, midline; hind lobe entire, raised, lateral lobes vertical, semicircular, and continuous with smaller irregular v-shaped middle lobe (
<figureCitation box="[542,669,970,996]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–13" captionStartId="3.[151,269,1998,2022]" captionTargetBox="[179,1413,428,1986]" captionTargetId="figure-115@3.[171,1417,391,2007]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–13. 1–9. hind lobe of prothorax, antero-lateral view; 10–12: same, lateral view; 13: same dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302140" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302140/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">Figs. 6, 13</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,634,1780]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">
Synthorax as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gonzalez-Soriano" authorityYear="2010" box="[392,522,1008,1033]" class="Insecta" family="Amphipterygidae" genus="Amphipteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nataliae">
<emphasis box="[392,522,1008,1033]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">A. nataliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but with second and third lateral stripe on middle of mesepimeron separated into a series of irregular spots on mesinfraepisternum; first lateral stripe reduced, its upper portion limited to upper fourth of mesepisternum followed ventrally by a small, elongate black spot ending at mesinfraepisternum; second (interpleural) thoracic stripe abbreviated and confined to metapleural fossa and small elongate spot above metastigma, third stripe bordering posterior margin of metepimeron. Coxae and legs as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gonzalez-Soriano" authorityYear="2010" box="[265,393,1195,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Amphipterygidae" genus="Amphipteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nataliae">
<emphasis box="[265,393,1195,1220]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">A. nataliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but femora dark brown; Wings (Fig. 17) hyaline; Ax Fw 8 (left):7 (right); Hw 7:7; Px Fw 34:35; Hw 26:28. Abdomen as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gonzalez-Soriano" authorityYear="2010" box="[557,688,1232,1257]" class="Insecta" family="Amphipterygidae" genus="Amphipteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nataliae">
<emphasis box="[557,688,1232,1257]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">A. nataliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but S3–6 with only a basal pale spot laterally, these becoming successively smaller on more terminal segments; S7 black, dorsum of S8–10 pale blue, a thin mid-dorsal black line on S10, its postero-dorsal margin with a narrow median notch half as long as segment. Genital ligula as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gonzalez-Soriano" authorityYear="2010" box="[300,438,1344,1369]" class="Insecta" family="Amphipterygidae" genus="Amphipteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="12" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nataliae">
<emphasis box="[300,438,1344,1369]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">A. nataliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[457,612,1344,1370]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–23" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1903,1927]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,605,1842]" captionTargetId="figure-198@6.[168,1419,605,1882]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 18–23. male accessory genitalia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302142" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302142/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">Figs. 22–23</figureCitation>
). Cercus black, slightly longer than S10, robust, spinulose dorsoexternally, in dorsal view fusiform with apex rounded and armed with a small internal anteapical scalariform tooth, medial surface anterior to tooth rugosely concave (
<figureCitation box="[838,938,1418,1444]" captionStart="FIGURES 24–27" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1966,1990]" captionTargetBox="[167,1425,189,1925]" captionTargetId="figure-22@7.[154,1433,176,1945]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 24–27. male caudal appendages, dorso-lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302144" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302144/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">Figs. 27</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[951,984,1418,1444]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–40" captionStartId="10.[151,270,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[175,1418,318,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-89@10.[163,1424,306,1867]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 32–40. 32–38. male caudal appendages, dorsal view; 39: tip of cercus, medio-ventral view; 40: female S9– 10, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302148" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302148/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">38</figureCitation>
); in lateral view cercus robust, linear, roughly parallel from base to apex, slightly swollen medially (
<figureCitation box="[881,968,1456,1482]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–31" captionStartId="9.[151,269,1755,1779]" captionTargetBox="[178,1424,216,1706]" captionTargetId="figure-123@9.[159,1428,194,1734]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 28–31. Male caudal appendages, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302146" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302146/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Paraproct about 0.70 length of cercus, its tip in lateral view slightly directed dorsally, base in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[995,1085,1493,1519]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–40" captionStartId="10.[151,270,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[175,1418,318,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-89@10.[163,1424,306,1867]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 32–40. 32–38. male caudal appendages, dorsal view; 39: tip of cercus, medio-ventral view; 40: female S9– 10, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302148" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302148/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
) inflated main branch short, parallel its apex slightly inflated, quadrate.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,634,1780]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,486,1567,1593]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">
Variation in 
<typeStatus box="[355,481,1567,1593]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">paratypes</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[494,595,1568,1594]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">paratype</typeStatus>
male like 
<typeStatus box="[717,819,1568,1594]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">holotype</typeStatus>
but with dark lateral thoracic stripes more extensive and complete.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,634,1780]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,350,1642,1668]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">Dimensions.</emphasis>
Males (
<emphasis box="[452,467,1643,1668]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">n</emphasis>
= 2, including 
<typeStatus box="[658,764,1642,1668]" pageId="12" pageNumber="27">holotype</typeStatus>
; means in parentheses): Hw 36.0 (37.5); abdomen 40.0 (41.5); total length 51.0 (52.9).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
